cl-did - W3C DID Implementation for Common Lisp
===============================================

This software was extracted from the CLPIC (Common Lisp P2P Intellectual
Property Chain) project.

Original source: src/identity/did/
Original project: https://github.com/example/clpic

Cryptographic implementations (SHA-256, RIPEMD-160, secp256k1) are original
pure Common Lisp implementations based on public specifications:

- SHA-256: FIPS 180-4
- RIPEMD-160: ISO/IEC 10118-3:2004
- secp256k1: SEC 2: Recommended Elliptic Curve Domain Parameters

Standards compliance:
- W3C DID Core 1.0: https://www.w3.org/TR/did-core/
- did:key Method: https://w3c-ccg.github.io/did-method-key/
- did:web Method: https://w3c-ccg.github.io/did-method-web/
